premise_source_doc_sentence: Michael Stanley Dukakis  (  -LSB- dᵿˈkɑːkᵻs -RSB- born November 3 , 1933 , Greek : Δουκάκης  )  is an American politician who served as the 65th and 67th Governor of Massachusetts , from 1975 to 1979 and 1983 to 1991 respectively .
He is the longest-serving governor in Massachusetts history and only the second Greek-American governor in U.S. history , after Spiro Agnew .
He was nominated by the Democratic Party for president in the 1988 election , but lost to the Republican candidate , Vice President George H. W. Bush .
Bush ran with Indiana Senator Dan Quayle while Dukakis ran with Texas Senator Lloyd Bentsen .
Dukakis ran with Texas Senator Lloyd Bentsen , and Bush ran with Indiana Senator Dan Quayle .
